list - list is containar that contain the list of string & numbers
    
    list_Name = [ "bob","ram","jem" ]
    list_Age = [23,34, 24,]
    print (list_Name)
   
   To acces the sepereate element one by one
   print(list_Name[0]) // o/p - 'bob'
   print(list_Name[1:3]) o/p - 'ram' 'jem'
   
   list_Name.extend(list_Age) // .extend() is used to combine to 2 list in one
   
   list_Name.append("jpy") // used to add item into list at last
   
   list_Name.insert(1, "kalpesh") // used to add more item in the list at peticular index
   
   list_Name.remove("kalpesh") // used to remove the item from the list
   
   list_Name.clear() // used to clear the list
   
   list_Name.pop() // used to delete the last item from the list
   
   print(list_Name.index("bob")) //.index() used to get the index of itme in the list 
   
   list_Name.sort() // used to sort the item
  
   list_Name.reverse() // used to reverse the item into list present in the list
   
   list_Name1 = list_Name.copy()/// used to get the copy of the list into new list varible
   
