Dictinories -- Dictionaries are used to store data values in key:value pairs.
               A dictionary is a collection which is ordered*, changeable and do not allow duplicates.
Dict = {
    
    "k": "kalpesh",
    "a": "ashok",
    "r": "roshni",
    "j": "jyoti"
}

print(Dict.get('a'))  // .get() used to get word the by key 

